HEADWORD: Pudu
<hw>Pu"du</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
very small deer (<spn>Pudua humilis</spn>), native of the Chilian Andes.
It has simple spikelike antlers, only two or three inches
long.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

